I went with my 3 friends for our "last call"drink at 11pm (city restrictions due to the Covid-19 Virus) and, to toast bringing in the 2021 New Year.  It was my first time going there even though, I've lived the last 5 years 1 block away.  It was a friindly, neighborhood-type establishment with a mature (age- 30+) and regular clientele.  Bertha, herself, is a very nice hostess with the mostess.  The staff was polite and the dj was energetic for the occasion, keeping the music upbeat and the people happy and dancing.  I had a great time with my friends and a positive experience.  I rarely "go out" I   will come here again sometimes in the future. May they continue to prosper and have a great 2021!

This spot is for the older crowd like 40+. They play mostly local music and old school songs. I just turned 30 but my boyfriend and I had a great time. I'm an old soul. We were visiting New Orleans for my birthday week. Every Tuesday they have open bar from 7-10pm and it's only $10 ! Can't beat that! Anything you want to drink like beer, mixed drinks, and shots. The food is regular bar food and they do not have a big selection of options but good enough to eat. I had the Buffalo wings and French fries. Everyone was friendly and having a good time. Dancing and partying. It's an urban environment so if being around black people makes you uncomfortable do not go. I am black so I love being around my people. Relaxed environment where you can go outside with your drink and come back in as you please.  They do not have enough seating which is the only bad part.
